{
  "stem": "26276.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if a thousand died one day, a thousand would be replaced the next day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had a quota to keep so many prisoners in that camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I heard, after the liberation, while I was still in Dachau, that Dachau was all dynamited the day before.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had to wait for a order to push one button to blow up the whole camp with all the prisoners in it because their command was that there should be no prisoner left alive in that camp.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If the Germans saw that they have no-- by the end of the war, to push the button to blow up the whole camp that there shouldn't be a sign of all that went on in there.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One of the soldiers-- towards the end, they had a lot of older soldiers in the army-- some of them even 65 years old or so.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They would put a uniform on them and they would give them a rifle from the First World War because they were already short on rifles, and he would be a guard-like, you know, because all the younger ones, they had to send to the front lines.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the older ones, they would guard us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So one of those guys, he found out that the camp is dynamited.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He went towards the front line on a bicycle to warn the Allied troops.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If they want to find Dachau in tact with all the prisoners, they should change their route to get as fast as possible towards Dachau.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Otherwise, the next few hours, there's nobody going to be left in the camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that was that surprise that morning where the American army came in unexpectedly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was the end of the--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His wife was there, and I saw one daughter.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
